<seg id=1> Huang Sihua: Creating Favorable Environment Next Year, Malaysia Determined to Retain 10b Lingji of Foreign Funds on Stock Market </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Kuala Lumpur) Malaysian Deputy Finance Minister Huang Sihua said that, because when the foreign control measures will have worked for a year by September 1 next year, it is expected that foreign funds of over 10 billion Lingji might be withdrawn from the stock market, the government will take various measures to create favorable investment environments and encourage foreign funds to continue staying in Malaysia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said that judging from the third quarter's economic growth rate, the economy in Malaysia has shown signs of recovery, believing that next September the econnomy will get stable, market activities will have regained vigor and foreign businessmen will also decide to make investments in Malaysia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The day before yesterday Huang Sihua made a speech at the economic report meeting and exchange meeting with Malaysian Chinese Federation of Industry and Commerce. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He stressed that Malaysian government has fixed the exchange rate of Malaysian currency at one US dollar to 3.8 Lingji, which will encourage investors to engineer long-term investment plans and make more accurate investment decisions, without the need to worry about fluctuations of the currency. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He said that the control measures will last a period of time until the international money market stabilizes, international organizations ought to set up a system to control speculative activities and the transparency of money transactions, and gurantee to eschew another financial storm attack on Southeast Asian region. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> On the other hand, Huang Sihua said that through coordinations by Finance Ministry, at home 20% of companies that have applied for loans but been disapproved and complained to Finance Ministry about this have got approval. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> He said that Finance Ministry will continue supplying consultancy or relevant aids to those companies that have applied for loans but failed, which will enable the companies wishing to materialize their development plans to go ahead smoothly with their plans and in turn will boost domestic economic and market activities. </seg>
</p>
